      acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'The recommended daily allowance (RDA) for calcium is: 1,000mg for adults ages 19-50, 1,000mg for men ages 51-70, 1,200mg for women ages 51+ and men ages 71+, and 1,300mg for adolescents. Most American adults consume 700-900mg of calcium through food daily. A calcium gummy providing 200-500mg can bridge the gap between dietary intake and the RDA. Taking more than 500mg of supplemental calcium at once reduces absorption — split doses are more effective.' },
    },
